    "updated_at": "2017-06-19T10:02:40Z",
    "body": "@zcbenz \r\n\r\n > The former is not on our plan, and the latter *[provide an API to create a custom dialog with a progress bar in it]* is simply impossible to satisfy all use cases. So I'm closing this as won't fix.\r\n\r\nWith all due respect, so is having a chrome without configurable attributes, such as color, yet it's still in the box. Sure, you can roll with your own chrome using a renderer process, but the same goes for a progress bar: native progress dialog if it fits your needs (perhaps with some configuration options), roll with your own if it does not."
